//Rupture medial retinaculum

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 - Femoropatellar joint of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Rupture medial retinaculum' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Contusion edema medial patella' checkbox is enabled
And 'Avulsion medial patella' checkbox is enabled
And 'Contusion edema lateral femoral condyle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteochondral lesion inferomedial patella' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteochondral lesion of lateral femoral condyle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Loose body' checkbox is enabled
And 'Medial patellofemoral ligament rupture (MPFL)' checkbox is enabled


And 'Lateral subluxation' radio button is enabled
And 'Lateral luxation' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Medial patellofemoral ligament rupture (MPFL)' checkbox
Then 'Patellar' radio button is enabled
And 'Midsubstance' radio button is enabled
Then 'Femoral' radio button is enabled
